<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9795920142212></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9795920142212><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9795920142212>Why I love being a Shaman</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9795920142212#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=12608><span id=Scholar>XanPrime</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>16 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 15th 8:55 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>My Shaman character Itarax is my second character on EQ, the first being a monk on a different server (I didn't want to be tempted to twink).&nbsp;&nbsp;I've got to say that choosing a Shaman as my second character was a smart move.  <br><br>I've appreciated how Verant balances each of the classes so that they have their own degrees of self-sufficiency (I'm sure I'll get flamed there, but that's the way I see it) but being a Shaman has added a new perspective on that since the Monk point of view.  I can do my own buffs and SoWs (and discovered the wonder of "gate").  No longer do I have to wait for that post on the OOC channel "Giving away SoWs at tunnel", etc.  I actually have services that others want...as a monk I was lucky to get in a group as a tank.  Even the monk's tailoring skill, selling the stuff was next to impossible. As a Shaman, my goods are my magic and (eventually, not there yet) Alchemy.<br><br>I also like the fact that I do have spells in the first place.  They're not top of the line in every department, mind you, but with a few quick switches I have just the combo I need.  Sure, that I have spells, I sacrificed combat ability but in the end (and at later levels) the tanks will need the casters more than the casters will need the tanks.<br><br>Just my two cents there, flame away or agree...I'm glad I have a Shaman out there. :)<br>&nbsp;<br>======================<br>Madrigan 35 Erudite Magician<br>Itarax 40 Iksar Shaman<br>Vetachi 18 Iksar Monk<br>Balorin 16 Halfling Rogue</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
