<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97957694220293></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97957694220293><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=97957694220293>Iksar Shaman</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=97957694220293#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=18642><span id=Scholar>Yilar</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>28 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 15th 4:44 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi all,<br><br>Recently started a Iksar Shaman and thought that I would let other share some of my experiences.<br><br>In cabilis East: (Allakhazam (C))<br>Klok Mugruk gives you an 8 item backpack to fill with Curscale Skins from Scaled Wolf Pups and Cubs. Combine them and return the pack for small coin and a piece of Curscale armor, which is excellent armor for a newbie. This quest gives very good experience (almost a bubble of experience at low levels). The following factions improve: CabilisResidents and LegionOfCabilis. <br><br>Make sure you get some backpacks as fast as you can so you can do the quest multiple times each run into Cabalis. Watch out for the Iksar bandits that do run through the newbie zone!<br><br>After you hit lvl 7 with this method get down to the pit, follow the path out from Cabilis in Field of Bone and most things there will be white to yellow and blue. I teamed up with someone there which makes the going a lot better..<br><br>Another good spot but this will be a bit slower, but good to do if the field of bone is teeming with Hatchling Iksars, is to go into Swamp of No hope, follow the path through the first bit of water. On this island will spawn the following Frogloks: Froglok Skipper, Escort, Escaped Froglok and Fisher..<br>The items that drop of these critters can be turned in for a quest again which will give nice XP:<br><a href="http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/quest.html?quest=223" target=_new>http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/quest.html?quest=223</a><br><br>Got me to lvl 7 in about three hours, good luck!<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
