<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9794884933194></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9794884933194><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9794884933194>RE: Weapon for Shaman</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9794884933194#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>149 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jan 14th 4:10 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I do not know about the general opinion, but if it is 2h Blunt is the way to go.... *shrug*&nbsp;&nbsp;Yes, there are some very nice 2h Blunt weapons out there.  Yes you can hit for some nice damage with them.  And Yes, you &gt;will&lt; be kicked out of higher level groups for meleeing except in candy arsed situations.  Let's see.  Hit for 200 points over the course of a fight (if you are lucky).  Or cast Alacrity (quickness) on three tanks, slow the mob and med.  Hmmmmm.  Not a hard situation to guess which one is better.<br><br>At lower levels, your choice of a weapon is not a huge deal.  At level 14, wading in with a 22 dmg 2h blunt and smacking stuff for 39 (due to the cap)is a nice bonus to the group.  That same weapon at level 50 doing maybe 55 points (no cap and bonuses) per swing, when and IF you hit, is of no consequence compared to your casting abilities.  Watch any well equipped tank class dish out closer to 200 points (or more) in the same amount of time it took you to swing, once, and miss more than likely.  Now, think of them with alacrity and being 30 or 40% faster.....<br><br>A 1h weapon (blunt or piercing) allows you to use a shield.  Getting AC 10 (raw points) and 9 wis from a Charred Guardian Shield and 6 more wis from a Jade Prod will more than make up for the "lack" of hitting power.  15 Wisdom and about 17 points of AC is hard to dispute.  How many 2h blunt (non Dragon or God loot) can do that?  And these are just some of the easier items to get on an established server.  That 15 wisdom will give you more mana, and reduce fizzles a little.  That 10 AC (raw, more likely about 16 to 18 in reality) will help save your life when the mob decides to aggro on you, or brings a buddy, and you just can't see to get a root to stick to park him...<br><br>To summarize, IN MY OPINION, below level 30, have fun and use whatever you want.  After 30 though, start going for a weapon/shield combination.  It will serve you better in the long run.<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman Bristlebane<br>Semi retired playing a monk.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
