	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree with Gorthin's thoughtful response. That is my experience with grouping as well.<br><br>I frequently melee when soloing, however, and weapon choice earlier may ease some of the pain later. The epic weapon for the shaman is a very nice spear which can do up to 20 to 30% of the damage to a mob in a solo situation. You could certainly wait to gain skill in piercing until the Spear of Fate is in your hands, but switching between the different weapon types in your formative years will help later on. Intermixing soloing and grouping will also help your defense skill, which translates directly to AC, making you hardier, and more versatile, later in your life.<br><br>Moohead<br>46 Ogre shaman, E'ci<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
