	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm only a mid level shaman, but from what i've read on many places, and after looking throuhg all the 2hb, 1hb, and peircing weapons for a shm, i have figured this out......... its up to you really. <br> 1hb, i dont use this much, except that there are tons of cheap 1hb you can use, whereas most peircers are pretty expensive. I used a screaming mace or Enamled Black mace for my 1hb, just when i couldnt afford anyhting else.<br> 2hb, if you know how to use this its pretty good actually, but only when soloing. 2hb generally has HUGE dly's (i used a gatorsmash 30dmg/70dly!) and the dmg cap makes the weapon more like 10/70dly! NOT GOOD!However what you are SUPPOSED to do is swing, cast during dly, then swing, cast during dly, and so on. Like i said earlier this is mainly for soloers who tank. <br> Piercing- This is the best choice in my opinion, but i use all of the skills. And as stated above most Wis giving or magic Spears are pretty darn expansive to most shaman under level 25 when they can go to cazic and make te big bucks. Ebon war spear is aroung 400pp-800pp on my server, and thats the lowest one i can find, i presently use a Jade prod as main melee, Charred Gaurdian shield or Testament of Venear (+10 wis, +10 mana i believe), and Ebon War spear in range. I use my CGS when i know im going to be hit, but i use my testament for when we have some good tanks who know to keep that taunt skill maxed!<br>Anyways this is jsut my opinoin, i know many shm with total different opinions<br><br>Nitsujlak Barshemguud<br>27th going on 60th shaman of War<br>Prexus server<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
