	   <tr><td colspan=2>Do not also forget the third most important thing tanks have behind #1) Armor Class #)2 High hit points.&nbsp;&nbsp;Their defensive skills (dodge, parry, block, riposte).  Yes, we get dodge at 15, but it caps at &gt;75&lt;.  The same level at which a monk will be maxxed out at level 16 (and we will hit our cap).  But thiers can go a LOT higher.  Just depending on AC, and a defensive skill equal to one skill of a level 16 tank will get you killed (except when you slow stuff, which will make a HUGE difference).<br><br>My monk, at 27, Dodges about 5% of the time and blocks about 10%.  So I neutralize 15% of the hits coming my way, BEFORE armor class is considered.  And I do not even have Riposte yet (level 35).  A shaman with a capped skill of 75 will dodge about 1% from my experiences.  Yes, 1% (at higher levels at least), no joke.  And that can be considered generous.<br><br>If we do not cast slow spells, and debuffers, our life expectency as a tank is pretty low.  Especially when talking about stuff that can Quad hit for well over 200 a pop (Frosticubes in Icewell keep come to mind).  Yes, I tanked these a couple times, but only after it was slowed and debuffed.  And it still took all a 60 level cleric had to keep me alive, even with an 870 AC and my skill 75 dodge =P<br><br>So while at lower levels we can play the main tank thing without relying on our spells giving us the edge, without AC, hp, and defensive skills, at higher levels, we are just a speed bump.<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman Bristlebane<br>Semi retired playing a monk<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
