<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97835231225465></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97835231225465><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=97835231225465>RE: Newbie Question</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=97835231225465#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 1st 12:33 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Kitting is a limited concept, and is not the best way for a shaman to solo.&nbsp;&nbsp;To solo as a shaman you<br>should take advantage of your strengths<br>Melee, dots, buffing, debuffing, and your pet.<br><br>for lvl 1 to 13 self buff, attack, slow mob if it<br>is attacking to fast, cast dd while beating on the mob with your 2hb or weapon of choice.  <br><br>lvl 14 to 23 self buff, Kite with  your new DD until you have only enough mana to dot and cast slow on the mob, then beat it to death with the 2hb.  Also do the totemic armor quest, if you want to solo you need the ac more than the wis at this point.  These are quite possibly the hardest lvl for a shaman to solo.<br><br>lvl 24 to 33<br>At last you get the spell that make the shaman one of the best soloing classes.  No, you can not kill yellow and reds, but you can kill almost anywhere. <br>Self buff, cast regen and speed on yourself, slow and dubble dot the mob.  Reapply poision dot as needed, beat the mob to death with your 2hb.<br><br>lvl 34 +<br>Same as lvl 33 except cast speed, str, and dex buffs on pet.  Pull with slow, let the pet have the mob cast sickness dot, (mob should stay on pet) cast poision dot. (mob will attack you) Take the damage as you and the pet melee the mob.  Recast poision dot as needed.<br><br>A note on melee buffs<br>Str inproves how often you hit and the amount of damage you do.<br>Dex improves how much damage you do and perhaps how often you hit.<br>Agi reduces the damage you take and how often you get hit. <br>Sta give you more hit points, (good buff at higher lvl) and alows you to fight longer, but as a shaman the fight will be over long before you need to be concerned.<br><br>A note on weapons<br>Ever since Kunark there have been some great spears and 1hb weapons with good damage and great wisdom.  However while soloing the damage done by the weapon is far more important that any wis gained.  And the new 2hb's (since Kunark) are by far the best damage weapons in the game for a shaman.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
