	   <tr><td colspan=2>Even more important for kiting than SoW is Snare/Ensnare.&nbsp;&nbsp;As Shamen, we do not get this ability.  So, DD kiting, while possible, is MUCH tougher for us.  We just do not have the room for error.  Root/DoT is better overall, anyway, especially for Shamen, as our DD does not have the mana efficiency needed to make kiting with it viable.<br><br>And just to let you know, I do not consider DoT kiting viable really anymore since the nerf a long time ago.  If your DoT while kiting has the same mana efficiency as the DD, why bother?  At best, pull with a DoT, then DD kite.  But like I said, Root/Dot is better IMO.<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman Bristlebane<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
