	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;   I'm just hitting level 12 as a barbarian shaman and if I knew then what I know now I would have done things a bit differently. If you are playing a shaman then here are some suggestions.<br>     First, print a map from this site of the area you are going to be operating in. Second, pull up a listing of every quest listed in your area and read every one of them. There may be a few that will help you get gear and are relatively easy to do (I still wish I had known about the Initiates Symbol of the Tribunal quest much earlier in my career). Third, don't wander outside the area that you are actually familiar with. It can be very easy to get lost in the wilderness. And, if you die out there, it can be a major pain in the butt finding your corpse.<br>     These are actually good things to do for any class.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
