	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, the polar bear skin quest from Cindl in the Kilt shop is great at low levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;It provides exp and a full suit of large patchwork very quickly.  Everfrost is a tough place to solo at low levels, because there are so many aggro mobs that gang up on you. Up to level 4, just use your little dd to pull mobs from the "highway"back into the enterance to Halas, so that their friends don't join in.  Thi ice goblin necklace quest in the Pit of Doom is also good - talk to the female guild master for the container you need.    From 5 you can hunt the outside of Blackburrow if you are careful not to pull too many at once.  The plains of Everfrost are always an option, as are some of the ice goblin igloos.  When hunting the plains, stay aware of what's going on around you!  To be honest, grouping is much safer...<br><br>Once you reach 5 and buy Gate, you can also do the Initiate Symbol of the Tribunal quest for a neck item that lets you summon a decent magic hammer.  Combine that with the two quests to West Karanas (from the food mercahnt near the water and the woman in the potion shop), and maybe a mail quest.  Collect any gnoll fangs and either hand them in in the Pit of Doom, on to the Captain in the Qeynos arena.  (The Qeynos rewards are a bit better.)<br><br>Good luck!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
